com.shop.cache.api.client.main
Class SCCacheObject<T>

java.lang.Object
  com.shop.cache.api.client.main.SCCacheObject<T>

public class SCCacheObject<T>
extends java.lang.Object

High-level caching API. Combined with the SCCacheObjectBuilder functor, makes easier the process of checking for an object in the cache and creating a new one if not in the cache.

The canonical form of use is: 

SCCacheObject         cacher = new SCCacheObject
(
        myCache,
        new SCDataBlock(myKey),
        new SCCacheObjectBuilder()
        {
                @Override
                public MyObject buildObject() throws Exception
                {
                        // ....
                        return newMyObject;
                }
        }
);
 MyObject               obj = cacher.get();

Method Detail

force

public SCCacheObject<T> force()
Causes get() to always create a new object, regardless if there's an existing object in the cache

Returns:
this

get

public T get()
      throws java.lang.Exception
Perform the get. An attempt is made to retrieve the object from the cache. If not found or stale, the builder will be called to generate a new object. That object will then be put into the cache.

Returns:
the cached object or a newly created object
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - errors

isFromCache

public boolean isFromCache()
Returns true if the object returned by get() was from the cache (as opposed to being newly created). Only valid after get() has been called

Returns:
true/false
